text:
The cleanUp() method in Zip.java of the Zip task does the following:

    protected void cleanUp() {
        addedDirs = new Hashtable();
        addedFiles = new Vector();
    }

It does not reset the 'filesets' variable.  As a result, when the instance
is reused to zip some other files, the files zipped in the prior usage are
included in later usages too.  The clenaUp() method should have been as 
follows:


    protected void cleanUp() {
        addedDirs = new Hashtable();
        addedFiles = new Vector();
        filesets = new Vector();
    }

Thank you for your attention.
